2026-03-02 22:33:30.541 | INFO     | app.agent.toolcall:think:143 - 🔧 Tool arguments: {"code": "text = \"The Committee currently anticipates that, even after employment and inflation are near mandate-consistent levels, economic conditions may, for some time, warrant keeping the target federal funds rate below levels the Committee views as normal in the longer run.\"\n\n# Determine if the text indicates a hawkish, dovish, or neutral stance\n# A hawkish stance typically involves tightening monetary policy (raising interest rates or reducing money supply)\n# A dovish stance typically involves easing monetary policy (lowering interest rates or increasing money supply)\n# Neutral means the stance is not clearly tightening or easing\n\n# Keywords for hawkish stance\nhawkish_keywords = [\"tightening\", \"raising\", \"increase\", \"higher\", \"constricting\", \"restricting\"]\n\n# Keywords for dovish stance\n dovish_keywords = [\"easing\", \"lowering\", \"decrease\", \"lower\", \"reduce\", \"relaxing\", \"loosening\"]\n\n# Check for hawkish keywords\nis_hawkish = any(keyword in text.lower() for keyword in hawkish_keywords)\n\n# Check for dovish keywords\nis_dovish = any(keyword in text.lower() for keyword in dovish_keywords)\n\n# Determine the stance based on the presence of keywords\nif is_hawkish:\n    result = \"HAWKISH\"\nelif is_dovish:\n    result = \"DOVISH\"\nelse:\n    result = \"NEUTRAL\"\n\nprint(result)"}
